    "content": "<p></p><div class=\"blockIndicator standardNote\">\n<p>This content covers features introduced in <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Thunderbird/Releases/3\">Thunderbird 3</a></p>\n</div><p></p>\n\n<p>The</p>\n\n<p>Implemented via XPCOM service for <a class=\"internal\" href=\"/en/Toolkit_API/extIApplication\" title=\"en/Toolkit API/extIApplication\"><code>extIApplication</code></a>: see the instructions on the <a class=\"internal\" href=\"/en/Toolkit_API/FUEL\" title=\"en/FUEL\">FUEL</a> (Firefox), <a class=\"internal\" href=\"/en/Toolkit_API/STEEL\" title=\"en/Thunderbird/STEEL\">STEEL</a> (Thunderbird) and <a class=\"internal\" href=\"/en/Toolkit_API/SMILE\" title=\"en/SeaMonkey/SMILE\">SMILE</a> (SeaMonkey) pages.</p>\n\n<h2 class=\"editable\" id=\"Attributes\">Attributes</h2>\n\n<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td class=\"header\">Attribute</td>\n   <td class=\"header\">Type</td>\n   <td class=\"header\">Description</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>platformIsMac</code></td>\n   <td><code>readonly attribute boolean</code></td>\n   <td>Returns true if the application is running on a Mac OS X. This is intended for situations where Mac does things differently, e.g. The application doesn't support print preview on Mac because Mac provides a preview option in the print dialog.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><code>platformIsLinux</code></td>\n   <td><code>readonly attribute boolean</code></td>\n   <td>Returns true if the application is running on GNU/Linux or on UNIX <span class=\"inlineIndicator standardNote\">New in <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Thunderbird/Releases/20\">Thunderbird 20</a></span></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>",
